/PG188/XX/PR

A psalm of David, when he changed his appearance feigning

madness before the Philistine king Avimeleh/±, who sent him

on his way./PR

/PR

A blessing shall I speak for /SCT/XXHE /XXA/XXLMIGHTY/XX, at all times,/PR


always is Godòs praise upon my mouth./PR

By /SCT/XXHE /XXI/XXNCOMPARABLE/XX shall my soul celebrate,/PR


and may the humble hear it and rejoice./PR

Give greatness to /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXNE/XX along with me,/PR


and let us elevate the divine name in unison./PR

Deeply have I searched for /SCT/XXHE /XXI/XXNEFFABLE/XX,/PR


and in all my trials, God has rescued me./PR

Have eyes turned toward God and be enlightened!/PR


Oh, let not your faces darken in confusion!/PR

Zero this person had, but when he called, /SCG/XXOD/XX listened,/PR


and in all his troubles, he was helped!/PR

He had an angel of /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXNE/XX stationed around him,/PR


as around all those who fear /SCG/XXOD/XX and are freed./PR

Taste then, and see how good /SCT/XXHE /XXF/XXOUNT/XX can be,/PR


how happy is the person who finds refuge there./PR

You holy beings, have awe of /SCT/XXHE /XXD/XXIVINE/XX/PR


there is no lack for those who tremble at it./PR

Cubs of the lion are at times in need and hungry,/PR


but those who ask of /SCG/XXOD/XX shall never lack the good./PR

Listen children, hear me out,/PR


an awe for /SCT/XXHE /XXM/XXYSTERIOUS/XX Iòll teach to you./PR

Might there be a person who wants life,/PR


who desires days of seeking good?/PR

Never let your tongue speak evil,/PR


nor your lips pronounce deceit!/PR

Swerve away from evil, perform good,/PR


seek peace, and follow after it./PI/PR

