/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. "Will be summoned to account"..."triumph over guilt"-
--the Hebrew verb is the same in both verses: /ITyeshamu...lo ye/UNshe/XXmu/XX. The
rendering of these phrases is meant to capture the paradoxical theological
and psychological implications of guilt: considered as a condition of
responsibility before God, the concept of guilt is an important cornerstone
of religious belief; considered as an emotion that can, sometimes inappro-
priately, lead a person into despair or self-hatred, a sense of guilt can some-
times be dangerous and wrong. Those who "triumph over" guilt master
the crippling effects of guilt as an emotion; they will, however, retain their
sense of right and wrong, and continue to hold themselves responsible
before God.    /SC/XXJ.R./XX/PR

