/PG198/XX/PR

No evil shall befall you,/PR

nor shall any plague approach your tent./PR

/PR

For God shall bid the angels to you,/PR

to protect you upon all your paths./PR

/PR

On divine hands you shall be carried,/PR

lest your foot should strike the rock./PR

/PR

On roaring lion and on python you shall tread,/PR

youòll trample cub and crocodile./PR

/PR

Yes, in Me is her desire, I help her to survive,/PR

I shall exalt her, for she knows my name./PR

/PR

He calls to Me, I answer him,/PR

with him am I in time of trial./PR

I release him, and I pay him honor./PR

/PR

Long are the days I satisfy her with,/PR

I look upon her with my saving help./PR

/PR

Long are the days I satisfy him with,/PR

I look upon him with my saving help./PR

